author: Khaleda Rahman
title: Georgia Gov. Brian Kemp Says He Didn't Know Asymptomatic People Could Transmit Coronavirus
description: Kemp said he would sign a state-wide shelter-in-place order to curb the spread of the coronavirus.
content:
Georgia Gov. Brian Kemp said he wasn't aware that asymptomatic people could transmit coronavirus as he announced he was preparing to issue a state-wide shelter-in-place order.
